1. If there is something you want to query often it could save time to create a view instead and avoid doing the same query multiple times. They make an easy font to a query that can be very complex. 

2. Non materialized stores only the query command while materialized stores both the query and the data itself.

3. Materialized can be worth it if you query something often and want to lower the time it takes to query. 

4. They take up less data storage and you dont have to update them everytime you update the base tables.